<HEADLINE> No. 22 UC Santa Barbara Wins  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Tawnee Cooper had 20 points to lead No. 22 UC
Santa Barbara with 20 points for a 89-59 victory over Loyola Marymount on Sunday
night.
</P>
<P>
	   Cooper scored 18 in the second half for UC Santa Barbara (10-3), which won
its seventh straight.
</P>
<P>
	   Kristi Rohr had 18 points and 10 rebounds, while Erin Buescher added 15
points and 10 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
	   UC Santa Barbara led the game 49-25 at halftime and increased its lead to a
game-high 35 points, with 6:20 remaining in the second half to bring the score
to 80-45. Loyola (7-5) was unable to catch up, losing by 30 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Loyola Marymount was led by Bryn Britton with 23 points and Rosa Bernasconi
with 22, including two 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
	   The Gauchos shot 56.3 percent from the floor, while Loyola Marymount was
held to 35.9 percent from the floor.
</P>
</TEXT>
