<BODY>
<HEADLINE> P&AMP;G May Sell 2 Skin Product Lines  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    CINCINNATI (AP) -- Procter &AMP; Gamble Co. is exploring selling two lines of
skin-cleansing products in order to concentrate on its Clearasil and Oil of Olay
brands.
</P>
<P>
	   P&AMP;G is soliciting bids for its Biactol product line that is sold in France
and Topexan line sold in Italy, management said Monday. The products are
marketed to teens to fight acne.
</P>
<P>
	   The company said it will keep the brands if it does not receive an
acceptable offer.
</P>
<P>
	   If the brands are sold, the employees now working on those products would be
moved into other P&AMP;G jobs, management said.
</P>
<P>
	   Biactol and Topexan represented less than 1 percent of P&AMP;G's total global
beauty products sales in fiscal 1998-99, which ended June 30. The company's
total worldwide sales for that year totaled $38.1 billion.
</P>
<P>
	   The Cincinnati-based consumer products company has been selling brands in
recent years that do not fit into P&AMP;G's long-term business plans.
</P>
<P>
	   Management said it wants to focus on brands with potential for increases in
global sales, including Clearasil and Oil of Olay.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
