<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Both Mixed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed higher against other major
currencies in European trading today. Gold was also mixed.
</P>
<P>
	   The euro was quoted at $1.0261 in late European trading, down from $1.0288
Friday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro traded at $1.0240.
</P>
<P>
	   Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday, included 105.31
Japanese yen, down from 105.40; 1.5676 Swiss francs, up from 1.5622; 1.4548
Canadian dollars, down from 1.4570.
</P>
<P>
	   The British pound was quoted at $1.6368, down from $1.6376.
</P>
<P>
	   In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 105.19 yen, and the pound
was worth $1.6376.
</P>
<P>
	   Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no longer
traded separately, though they remain in use.
</P>
<P>
	   Based on euro rates, the dollar is worth 1.9070 German marks, up from
1.9007; 6.3933 French francs, up from 6.3766; 2.1481 Dutch guilders, up from
2.1424; 1887.75 Italian lire, up from 1882.07
</P>
<P>
	   Gold closed in London at $282.25 bid per troy ounce, up from $281.90 on
Friday. In Zurich the bid price was $281.40 unchanged from $281.40. Gold fell 60
cents in Hong Kong to 281.45.
</P>
<P>
	   Silver opened in London at $5.20 bid per troy ounce, up from $5.14.
</P>
</TEXT>
