<HEADLINE> European Stocks Close Higher  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    LONDON (AP) -- Gains in telecommunications and telecom stocks drove European
stock indexes higher Monday, boosted by merger plans between America Online Inc.
and media company Time Warner Inc.
</P>
<P>
	   AOL, the world's largest Internet service provider, is acquiring Time Warner
for more than $160 billion in stock.
</P>
<P>
	   Investors were spurred on by the prospect of similar mergers between leading
media and Internet players.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Stoxx Index of 606 European companies closed up 5.64 points at
365.39, while the Dow Jones Euro Stoxx Index, which tracks 324 companies in
countries joining the single currency, ended up 6.05 points at 401.40.
</P>
<P>
	   The media sector of the Dow Jones Stoxx Index overshadowed the rest of the
market with a massive 9.4 percent rise.
</P>
<P>
	   Media and technology heavyweights across Europe also climbed higher after
the merger announcement.
</P>
<P>
	   In London, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index closed up 1.6
percent at 6,607.7. Pearson Group was up 15.3 percent, EMI Group rose 15.3
percent and BSkyB was up 12.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   In Paris the CAC 40 index closed up 1.9 percent at 5,646.12 points. Pay-TV
company Canal Plus and Lagardere led media sector gains after news of a deal
between the two companies. Canal Plus closed 17.1 percent higher and Lagardere
closed 10.1 percent higher.
</P>
<P>
	   The Netherlands' benchmark 25-share AEX index closed up 1.6 percent at
655.14 and the Swiss Market Index closed 0.1 percent higher at 7,452.8.
</P>
<P>
	   Meanwhile, Frankfurt's Xetra DAX index closed up 2.1 percent at 6,925.52.
</P>
<P>
	   Other media and Internet darlings included Spanish Internet specialist Terra
Networks which rose 6.2 percent, Dutch publisher Wolters Kluwer, up 10 percent,
and Germany's SAP which gained 6.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   Milan's MIBtel index bucked the trend, however, falling 1.2 percent to
39,716. Although Internet stocks such as Aedes increased, investors opted to
take profits in selected telecoms and financial stocks.
</P>
<P>
	   The Dow Jones Euro Stoxx 50 Index finished up 65.8 points at 4,714, while
the DJ Stoxx 50 Index ended up 59.1 points at 4,511.6.
</P>
</TEXT>
