<HEADLINE> 'Stuart Little' Tops Box Office  </HEADLINE>
    By TOM HARRIGAN Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- "Stuart Little" led the movie box office for the third
time in the four weekends since it debuted, adding $11.2 million Friday through
Sunday to move above $95 million.
</P>
<P>
	   The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through Sunday, followed
by distributing studio, gross, number of theater locations, average receipts per
location, total gross and number of weeks in release, as compiled by Exhibitor
Relations Co. Inc. and ACNielsen EDI.
</P>
<P>
	   1. "Stuart Little," Sony, $11.2 million, 2,979 locations, $3,765 average,
$95.3 million, four weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   2. "The Green Mile," Warner Bros., $9.7 million, 2,678 locations, $3,634
average, $91.3 million, five weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   3. "The Talented Mr. Ripley," Paramount, $9.3 million, 2,316 locations,
$4,025 average, $54.2 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   4. "Any Given Sunday," Warner Bros., $8.8 million, 2,505 locations, $3,505
average, $59.2 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   5. "Galaxy Quest," DreamWorks, $8 million, 2,450 locations, $3,275 average,
$38.5 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   6. "Toy Story 2," Disney, $7.2 million, 2,752 locations, $2,599 average,
$219.7 million, eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   7. "Magnolia," New Line, $5.7 million, 1,034 locations, $5,507 average, $6.6
million, four weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   8. "Bicentennial Man," Disney, $5.3 million, 2,612 locations, $2,032
average, $47.2 million, four weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   9. "Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo," Disney, $5 million, 2,086 locations, $2,436
average, $54.1 million, five weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   10. "Snow Falling on Cedars," Universal, $3.9 million, 1,150 locations,
$3,400 average, $4.1 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   11. "Anna and the King," Fox, $3.6 million, 2,004 locations, $1,820 average,
$30.9 million, four weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   12. "Man on the Moon," Universal, $3.3 million, 2,085 locations, $1,610
average, $30.2 million, three weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   13. "The Cider House Rules," Miramax, $3.1 million, 816 locations, $3,771
average, $8.2 million, five weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   14. "Fantasia 2000," Disney, $2.6 million, 54 locations, $47,958 average,
$6.9 million, two weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   15. "The World is Not Enough," MGM, $1.8 million, 1,317 locations, $1,389
average, $120.9 million, eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   16. "Sleepy Hollow," Paramount, $1.1 million, 1,070 locations, $1,033
average, $94.7 million, eight weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   17. "End of Days," Universal, $841,455, 813 locations, $1,035 average, $64.5
million, seven weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   18. "The Hurricane," Universal, $703,575, 159 locations, $4,425 average,
$2.5 million, two weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   19. "The End of the Affair," Sony, $636,573, 92 locations, $6,919 average,
$2.4 million, six weeks.
</P>
<P>
	   20. "American Beauty," Dreamworks, $577,310, 289 locations, $1,998 average,
$71.9 million, 17 weeks.
</P>
