<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- Japanese stocks surged early Tuesday, bolstered by big gains
on Wall Street. The dollar was lower against the yen.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average climbed 518.88 points, or 2.85
percent, to 18,712.29 points in the first 30 minutes of trading. On Friday, the
average closed up 25.14 points, or 0.14 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar bought 105.24 yen, down 0.08 yen from late Friday in Tokyo but
above its late New York level of 105.20 yen overnight.
</P>
<P>
	   Financial markets in Tokyo were closed Monday for a national holiday.
</P>
<P>
	   On Tokyo's stock market, prices started higher Tuesday in post-holiday
trading, following a new closing high in the Dow Jones industrial average at
11,572.20 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
	   Early gainers in Tokyo included high-technology and communications issues,
which were boosted by gains in U.S. counterparts following news of a proposed
merger between America Online and Time Warner.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section was up 61.95 points, or 3.87 percent, to 1,660.96 points. The TOPIX
closed down 10.58 points, or 0.66 percent, on Friday
</P>
<P>
	   In currency dealings, though it fell from its Friday level in Tokyo, the
dollar edged higher compared with the New York level as demand for U.S. stocks
boosted buying of the greenback.
</P>
</TEXT>
