<HEADLINE> Tokyo Stocks Rise  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo share prices climbed Tuesday morning led by technology
issues and boosted by an overnight record closing on Wall Street. The dollar was
lower against the yen.
</P>
<P>
	   The benchmark 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average rose 575.32 points, or 3.16
percent, to 18,768.73 at the end of the morning session. On Friday, the average
closed up 25.14 points, or 0.14 percent.
</P>
<P>
	   The dollar bought 105.24 yen in late morning, down 0.08 yen from late Friday
in Tokyo but above its late New York level of 105.20 yen overnight.
</P>
<P>
	   Financial markets in Tokyo were closed Monday for a national holiday.
</P>
<P>
	   On Tokyo's stock market, prices rose sharply early Tuesday following a new
closing high in the Dow Jones industrial average at 11,572.20 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
	   Morning gainers in Tokyo included high-technology and communications issues,
which were boosted by gains in U.S. counterparts following news of a proposed
merger between America Online and Time Warner.
</P>
<P>
	   The broader Tokyo Stock Price Index of all issues listed on the first
section was up 74.85 points, or 4.68 percent, to 1,673.86 points. The TOPIX
closed down 10.58 points, or 0.66 percent, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
	   In currency dealings, though the dollar fell from its Friday level in Tokyo,
it edged higher compared with Monday's New York level as demand for U.S. stocks
supported buying of the greenback.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
