<HEADLINE> 3 Guatemalan Death Row Inmates Flee  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GUATEMALA CITY (AP) -- Three death row inmates were among 11 prisoners who
escaped from a prison Monday on the northern edge of Guatemala City.
</P>
<P>
	   The inmates, some armed with guns, took the prison director hostage and fled
in a food delivery truck. They released the director a few blocks away from
prison.
</P>
<P>
	   Officials said the 11 fugitives included three men who were awaiting death
by lethal injection: Elver Gabriel, Jorge Antonio Alvarado Garcia and Carlos
Eduardo Gonzalez Esquivel. All three had been convicted of kidnapping.
</P>
<P>
	   Police were searching for the escapees in northern Guatemala City and nearby
towns.
</P>
