<HEADLINE> No. 2 Tennessee 79, Arkansas 69  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    KNOXVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Kara Lawson scored a career-high 25 points and
Michelle Snow added 24 to lead No. 2 Tennessee to a 79-69 victory Monday night
over Arkansas.
</P>
<P>
	   The Lady Vols (12-2, 2-0 Southeastern Conference) rebounded from Saturday's
loss to No. 1 Connecticut despite a poor first-half performance that left them
trailing by 13 points at halftime. Arkansas (9-4, 0-1) was led by Wendi Willits
with 16 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Tennessee quickly recovered in the second half, using a 20-6 run in the
first 6-  1/2 minutes to retake the lead at 46-45. Lawson, who also had 10
rebounds, and Snow led the offensive charge, combining for 13 points in the
spurt.
</P>
<P>
