	   Tennessee was at its worst in the first half.
</P>
<P>
	   The Lady Vols struggled offensively the entire half, shooting just 27
percent from the field. Arkansas didn't shoot much better, but managed to stay
close and took its first lead at 9-8 on Celia Anderson's layup at 12:20.
</P>
<P>
	   Back-to-back 3-pointers by Tennessee's April McDivitt and Lawson allowed the
Lady Vols to regain the lead. But a 16-2 run by the Lady Razorbacks gave
Arkansas a 26-18 lead with 4:24 left in the half.
</P>
<P>
	   Tennessee fought back behind Lawson, who hit another 3-pointer and short
jump shot in the closing minutes. But Arkansas didn't wilt, outscoring the Lady
Vols 13-10 in a late first-half run that gave the Lady Razorbacks a 39-26
halftime lead.
</P>
